56:08.000 --> 56:13.000
If we take an electronic carrier,

56:13.000 --> 56:15.000
that is, some kind of electronic array of information,

56:15.000 --> 56:21.000
then the direction of protection is built on two strategic lines.

56:21.000 --> 56:25.000
That is, protection is built directly on access,

56:25.000 --> 56:27.000
in the form of access restrictions,

56:27.000 --> 56:29.000
in the form of electronic identifiers,

56:29.000 --> 56:33.000
in the form of some kind of biometric identity recognition systems.

56:33.000 --> 56:37.000
And the second direction is protection of the document itself.

56:37.000 --> 56:39.000
What cannot be done with paper.

56:39.000 --> 56:42.000
The protection of the document itself is mainly done with cryptography,

56:42.000 --> 56:45.000
that is, cryptographic means of protection.

56:45.000 --> 56:47.000
If in a simplified version,

56:47.000 --> 56:49.000
some information is taken,

56:49.000 --> 56:53.000
a kilobyte or megabyte of information is divided into 10 parts,

56:53.000 --> 56:57.000
all this is done in a very simplified version.

56:57.000 --> 56:59.000
These parts are re-piled up,

56:59.000 --> 57:01.000
the tenth part is on the second,

57:01.000 --> 57:03.000
the second part is on the fourth,

57:03.000 --> 57:05.000
the fourth part is on the first.

57:05.000 --> 57:07.000
Thus, a certain encryption of the document occurs.

57:07.000 --> 57:09.000
The value of the document is not lost from this.

57:09.000 --> 57:11.000
That is, it is possible to decrypt in the future,

57:11.000 --> 57:13.000
that is, to put these parts in place,

57:13.000 --> 57:15.000
and the value of the document will be preserved.

57:15.000 --> 57:17.000
That is, there will be the same document.

57:17.000 --> 57:19.000
What cannot be done with paper.

57:19.000 --> 57:21.000
You cannot tear it,

57:21.000 --> 57:23.000
re-pile it,

57:23.000 --> 57:25.000
preserving the value of the document.

57:25.000 --> 57:27.000
This is possible,

57:27.000 --> 57:29.000
